Durban - A pregnant woman was tied up in a house robbery in Hillcrest on Wednesday night. Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane, a KwaZulu-Natal police spokesperson, said the 34-year-old pregnant woman was at her home in Park Close when she was attacked by two robbers. Zwane said she was threatened with a knife and was tied up.  The robbers took goods from the house before they fled the scene. A case of house robbery was opened at Hillcrest. Police have not arrested anyone as yet. Zwane said the matter is under investigation. Shaun Lyle of the Hillcrest Park Neighbourhood Watch said one of the robbers carried a large knife. He said they took laptops, shoe, cash and rings from the woman. Last week, a 53-year-old woman tried to fight off two robbers in her Hillcrest home. She was stabbed in her arm. Colonel Thembeka Mbele, a KwaZulu-Natal police spokesperson, said the woman alleged that on Wednesday at 21:55, she was at her place of residence at Montrose Avenue in Hillcrest when she was held at knifepoint by two robbers. "The robbers stabbed her on the left arm before fleeing the scene with cash, a handbag and cellphone," Mbele said Daily News